WEBVTT

00:01.918 --> 00:04.921
[adventurous music]

00:05.004 --> 00:12.011
♪ ♪

00:32.365 --> 00:33.283
- NO, NO, LOOK.

00:33.366 --> 00:34.617
YOU HAVE TO LISTEN TO ME,
PLEASE.

00:34.701 --> 00:37.078
DON'T PUT ON THAT MASK.

00:37.162 --> 00:38.121
- PUT IT ON.

00:38.204 --> 00:39.456
- THEN WILL YOU LIFT THE CURSE

00:39.539 --> 00:40.290
OFF MY GRAN AND MY FRIENDS?

00:40.373 --> 00:42.292
- YES.

00:42.375 --> 00:43.501
NOW PUT ON THE MASK.

00:44.502 --> 00:46.713
- NINA!

00:57.432 --> 00:59.392
- WHY IS NOTHING HAPPENING?

01:02.562 --> 01:05.815
YOU ARE NOT THE PARAGON.

01:05.899 --> 01:09.110
I SHALL HAVE TO SEEK
MY CHAMPION ELSEWHERE.

01:09.194 --> 01:12.489
YOU?
IT IS OVER.

01:12.572 --> 01:14.491
- [cries out]

01:14.574 --> 01:15.533
- WHAT IS IT?
WHAT'S WRONG?

01:15.617 --> 01:16.493
- NO, SENKHARA!

01:16.576 --> 01:18.369
SENKHARA, WAIT!

01:18.453 --> 01:19.788
PLEASE!

01:22.123 --> 01:24.292
MY LOCKET.
MY LOCKET!

01:24.375 --> 01:25.251
SOMETHING'S HAPPENING!

01:27.629 --> 01:28.254
[shimmering tone]

01:31.257 --> 01:32.675
THIS ISN'T THE TRUE MASK,
SENKHARA.

01:32.759 --> 01:34.594
THIS IS THE FINAL CLUE!

01:34.677 --> 01:36.763
IT WAS MEANT FOR ME.

01:36.846 --> 01:38.807
I AM THE ONE YOU NEED
TO STOP THIS.

01:38.890 --> 01:40.225
PLEASE!

01:47.440 --> 01:49.317
- READ.

01:51.778 --> 01:52.695
- "THE TRUE MASK STILL WAITS,

01:52.779 --> 01:55.240
"HIDDEN FOR ALL TO SEE.

01:55.323 --> 01:57.075
"THE PORTAL OF THE MIND AWAKES.

01:57.158 --> 01:58.326
THE PARAGON IS THE KEY."

02:04.999 --> 02:06.793
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

02:06.876 --> 02:08.794
- HOW CAN SOMETHING BE
"HIDDEN FOR ALL TO SEE"?

02:08.877 --> 02:10.713
- LIKE IN THE MUSEUM.

02:10.797 --> 02:13.258
THE BRONZE REPLICA.

02:13.341 --> 02:14.717
THE FROBISHER-SMYTHES DONATED IT

02:14.801 --> 02:16.135
TO THE BRITISH MUSEUM,
DIDN'T THEY?

02:16.219 --> 02:17.470
- YEAH, HIDDEN IN PLAIN SIGHT!

02:17.554 --> 02:18.721
- LET'S GO.

02:18.805 --> 02:20.723
- NO--NINA, THINK ABOUT
WHAT YOU'RE DOING!

02:24.686 --> 02:26.563
- JASPER.

02:29.107 --> 02:30.358
TRUDY?

02:30.441 --> 02:31.317
ANYBODY HERE?

02:33.862 --> 02:35.071
COAST IS CLEAR.

02:39.075 --> 02:39.909
- RUFUS.

02:39.993 --> 02:41.411
- HE'S COME BACK FOR THE MASK.

02:41.494 --> 02:42.954
- WELL, THEN, WE'LL LET HIM
GO DOWN AND GET IT

02:43.037 --> 02:44.080
WHILE WE TAKE THE REAL ONE.

02:44.163 --> 02:45.373
- NO, WE CAN'T DO THAT.

02:45.456 --> 02:48.793
- SO THAT'S THE WAY DOWN
TO THE TUNNELS.

02:48.877 --> 02:49.919
- BACK, BACK, BACK!

02:50.003 --> 02:51.379
WE'LL HAVE TO GO
BY THE ANTECHAMBER.

02:51.462 --> 02:53.631
- NO--NINA, WE NEED
TO TALK ABOUT THIS.

02:53.715 --> 02:55.341
- NO, NO, NO, WAIT.

02:55.425 --> 02:57.594
GO OUTSIDE AND KEEP WATCH.

02:57.677 --> 02:59.429
THIS ONE,
YOU'RE COMING WITH ME

02:59.512 --> 03:01.264
FOR A LITTLE INSURANCE POLICY.

03:01.347 --> 03:02.974
NO, BEFORE YOU GO,

03:03.057 --> 03:04.642
SHOW ME THE WAY
THROUGH THE TUNNEL.

03:04.726 --> 03:05.977
- OH...

03:11.482 --> 03:14.944
- THIS WAS A MAN
WHO HAD MADE SOME MISTAKES

03:15.028 --> 03:17.989
BUT WHO WANTED--
DESPERATELY WANTED--

03:18.072 --> 03:20.366
TO TURN HIS...

03:20.450 --> 03:21.743
TO MAKE...

03:23.703 --> 03:26.164
AND WHO...

03:28.041 --> 03:30.084
- GO ON, POPPS.

03:32.211 --> 03:37.926
- AND WHO WANTED,
MORE THAN ANYTHING,

03:38.009 --> 03:42.472
JUST TO BE OUR FATHER AGAIN.

03:42.555 --> 03:48.519
AND I REALIZED
I NEEDED TO HAVE MY DAD BACK.

03:53.983 --> 03:54.275
[sniffling]

03:56.569 --> 03:58.321
- THAT WAS A STATEMENT
READ ON BEHALF

03:58.404 --> 04:02.700
OF BOTH JOHN CLARKE'S CHILDREN,
JEROME AND POPPY CLARKE.

04:05.912 --> 04:07.205
- THANK YOU.

04:07.288 --> 04:10.708
I CAN'T BELIEVE GERBIL
WOULD LET US DOWN LIKE THIS.

04:10.792 --> 04:11.417
- I CAN.

04:13.586 --> 04:14.253
- REALLY NOT HELPING, MICK.

04:17.798 --> 04:19.634
- OF COURSE.

04:19.716 --> 04:24.722
THE WEEPING PARAGON
IS THE CHOSEN ONE.

04:26.265 --> 04:31.270
BUT THE MASK IN THE TUNNEL
HAS NO THIRD EYE.

04:33.439 --> 04:38.444
TIME TO TAKE ANOTHER LOOK,
CORBIERE, HMM?

04:41.114 --> 04:42.907
- [ghostly whispering]
CHOSEN ONE.

04:42.991 --> 04:43.866
- DID ANYONE ELSE HEAR THAT?

04:43.950 --> 04:44.951
WHO KEEPS WHISPERING?

04:45.034 --> 04:47.161
- LOOK, IT'S OKAY.

04:47.245 --> 04:48.579
I THINK YOU'VE STILL GOT
A CONCUSSION.

04:48.663 --> 04:49.706
- UH, MISS WILLIAMSON,

04:49.789 --> 04:52.875
WHAT EXACTLY IS GOING ON HERE,
PLEASE?

04:52.959 --> 04:54.711
- EDDIE HAD AN ACCIDENT...

04:54.794 --> 04:57.588
AND THE NURSE TOLD US
TO BRING HIM BACK HERE.

04:57.672 --> 04:59.007
- VERY WELL.
VERY WELL.

04:59.090 --> 04:59.966
COME ALONG.
OUT OF MY WAY.

05:00.049 --> 05:00.425
GO.
GO!

05:03.678 --> 05:04.762
- NO INTERROGATION?

05:04.846 --> 05:06.723
HUH.

05:06.806 --> 05:07.974
- THAT'S WEIRD.

05:08.057 --> 05:09.434
MAYBE VICTOR'S HAD
A BANG ON THE HEAD TOO.

05:09.517 --> 05:11.811
ANYWAY, I'M JUST GONNA GO
AND CHECK ON THE...

05:11.894 --> 05:12.562
- NO!

05:12.645 --> 05:15.023
YOU CAN'T GO THAT WAY,

05:15.106 --> 05:18.735
'CAUSE YOU DON'T HAVE
THE PERSON...

05:18.818 --> 05:21.070
TO OPEN THE THING.

05:21.154 --> 05:22.238
- OH!

05:22.322 --> 05:26.200
OH--OH, YOU MEAN, THE LOCK--
THE SOCKET.

05:26.284 --> 05:27.410
WELL, THAT'S FINE.

05:27.493 --> 05:30.288
WE'LL JUST GO
THE BACK WAY TO THE...

05:30.371 --> 05:33.249
THROUGH THE S...LYBERRY.

05:33.332 --> 05:37.003
- OKAY, GUYS, I'M CONCUSSED,

05:37.086 --> 05:40.631
AND I CAN STILL SEE THROUGH
YOUR OH-SO-SECRET CODE.

05:40.715 --> 05:41.883
- [snorts]
CODE.

05:41.966 --> 05:45.553
- OKAY, I AM GOING
TO MAKE SURE EDDIE IS OKAY.

05:45.636 --> 05:46.637
- YEAH.

05:46.721 --> 05:47.722
- AND THEN I WILL
CATCH UP WITH YOU.

05:47.805 --> 05:50.099
- COOL.

05:50.183 --> 05:50.433
- COME ON, AMBER.

05:54.729 --> 05:55.646
[gasps]

05:55.730 --> 05:56.647
- NINA!

05:56.731 --> 05:58.816
- ALFIE.

05:58.900 --> 05:59.942
- WE DIDN'T GET JEROME.

06:00.026 --> 06:01.402
RUFUS DROVE OFF WITH HIM.

06:01.486 --> 06:02.111
I THINK HE'S COMING
FOR THE MASK.

06:02.195 --> 06:04.072
- RUFUS IS ALREADY HERE.

06:04.155 --> 06:05.323
- WHAT?

06:05.406 --> 06:06.032
- HE'LL BE
IN THE MASK CHAMBER NOW.

06:06.115 --> 06:09.118
- IS JEROME WITH HIM?

06:09.202 --> 06:10.203
I NEED TO HELP HIM.

06:10.286 --> 06:11.954
- ALFIE, DON'T!

06:12.038 --> 06:13.372
- LOOK, BE CAREFUL, ALFIE.

06:13.456 --> 06:15.833
AND DON'T TRY ANYTHING STUPID.

06:15.917 --> 06:17.335
- IT'S ALFIE.

06:17.418 --> 06:20.797
OF COURSE HE'LL TRY
SOMETHING STUPID.

06:20.880 --> 06:22.548
- AMBER...
JUST MAKE SURE HE KNOWS

06:22.632 --> 06:24.133
THAT THE MASK DOWN THERE
IS FAKE.

06:25.885 --> 06:27.011
OKAY, LET'S GO
GET THE REAL MASK.

06:27.095 --> 06:28.971
- YEAH, LET'S GO.

06:36.521 --> 06:37.772
- STAY THERE!

06:42.652 --> 06:46.030
THE MASK OF ANUBIS.

06:46.114 --> 06:47.365
FINALLY.

06:47.448 --> 06:51.285
- AMBER MILLINGTON,
WHAT DO YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING?

06:51.369 --> 06:52.495
- VICTOR, WOW.

06:52.578 --> 06:54.330
[speaking indistinctly]

06:54.413 --> 06:55.498
- HELP ME--
[grunts]

06:57.959 --> 07:01.170
- RUFUS ZENO.

07:02.630 --> 07:06.717
THE FAKE OBITUARY WAS
A NICE TOUCH.

07:06.801 --> 07:10.596
AND THE ANONYMOUS TIP-OFF
REGARDING THE EXHIBITION.

07:10.680 --> 07:13.099
- OH, I'M GLAD YOU APPRECIATE
MY EFFORTS, VICTOR.

07:13.182 --> 07:14.142
AND VERA'S TOO.

07:14.225 --> 07:17.979
I THOUGHT YOU'D HIT IT OFF.

07:18.062 --> 07:20.648
NOW, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,
I HAVE RATHER AN EXCLUSIVE

07:20.731 --> 07:22.191
CEREMONY TO PERFORM.

07:22.275 --> 07:24.068
- IT WON'T WORK.

07:24.152 --> 07:26.696
- NICE TRY.

07:26.779 --> 07:30.700
- THE MASK IS MISSING
ITS THIRD EYE.

07:34.954 --> 07:37.165
- OF COURSE.
RUFUS REMOVED IT.

07:37.248 --> 07:39.584
HE'S REMOVED THE GEM.

07:41.961 --> 07:44.213
THE FROBISHER GEM...

07:44.297 --> 07:45.631
WHICH I HAVE IN MY SAFE.

07:48.092 --> 07:49.343
- GO!

07:50.595 --> 07:51.470
- NO!

07:51.554 --> 07:52.513
- YES!
NICE CATCH, ALFIE!

08:01.105 --> 08:02.481
- AHHH!

08:10.615 --> 08:13.326
- SO BASICALLY,
RUFUS IS A NUT JOB

08:13.409 --> 08:15.620
WHO WANTS ANYTHING CONNECTED
TO THE FROBISHER-SMYTHES.

08:15.703 --> 08:19.332
AND HE DOESN'T HAVE A PROBLEM
WITH KIDNAP AND STEALING.

08:19.415 --> 08:20.416
- YEAH, TELL ME ABOUT IT.

08:20.499 --> 08:23.377
- BUT WHY JEROME?

08:23.461 --> 08:26.631
RUFUS MUST HAVE THOUGHT
HE HAD SOMETHING THAT HE NEEDED.

08:26.714 --> 08:27.506
- MAYBE HE DID.

08:33.011 --> 08:33.888
[shimmering tone]

08:33.971 --> 08:34.972
OW.

08:35.056 --> 08:36.640
- WHOA.

08:36.724 --> 08:39.184
- OKAY, IT'S NEVER
DONE THAT BEFORE.

08:39.268 --> 08:40.519
CAREFUL.
CAREFUL, IT'S HOT.

08:40.602 --> 08:41.687
- NO, IT'S NOT.

08:41.770 --> 08:43.188
IT'S COLD.

08:44.190 --> 08:46.317
ISN'T THIS THE GEM

08:46.400 --> 08:47.109
THAT JEROME'S
BEEN OBSESSING ABOUT?

08:47.193 --> 08:49.779
WHERE'D YOU GET THIS?

08:49.862 --> 08:50.821
- FROM JEROME.

08:50.905 --> 08:51.989
HE GAVE IT TO ME IN THE BARN.

08:52.073 --> 08:53.991
DON'T ASK ME WHY.

08:55.326 --> 08:56.953
- [whispering]
OSIRIAN.

08:57.036 --> 08:59.705
CHOSEN ONE.

08:59.789 --> 09:00.456
- DO YOU HEAR THAT?

09:00.539 --> 09:03.251
- NO.
HEAR WHAT?

09:03.334 --> 09:04.627
- [whispering]
CHOSEN ONE...

09:04.710 --> 09:05.586
- CHOSEN ONE.

09:05.670 --> 09:07.630
- [whispering]
FIND NINA.

09:07.713 --> 09:08.798
- WHERE IS SHE?

09:08.881 --> 09:10.007
SHE NEEDS ME.

09:10.091 --> 09:12.176
- EDDIE, EDDIE, ARE YOU OKAY?

09:12.260 --> 09:13.302
- SHE NEEDS ME.

09:13.386 --> 09:13.803
I NEED TO FIND HER...

09:13.886 --> 09:15.930
NOW.

09:26.524 --> 09:29.652
- NINA, YOU DON'T
HAVE TO DO THIS.

09:29.735 --> 09:30.695
[door creaking]

09:30.778 --> 09:31.737
- I DO.

09:31.821 --> 09:33.030
- THE THIRD EYE!

09:33.114 --> 09:35.283
YOU NEED THE THIRD EYE.

09:35.366 --> 09:37.451
- MY DAD'S GEM.

09:37.535 --> 09:39.996
- TELL ME YOU STILL HAVE IT,
JEROME.

09:40.079 --> 09:41.664
- NO, I GAVE IT TO--

09:43.499 --> 09:45.126
- EDDIE?

09:45.209 --> 09:46.961
- HE JUST STARTED
FREAKING OUT ON ME,

09:47.044 --> 09:48.004
MUMBLING ABOUT THE CHOSEN ONE
AND THE--

09:48.087 --> 09:49.672
THE OSIRIAN.

09:49.755 --> 09:52.508
I THINK IT MUST BE
THE BANG ON THE HEAD.

09:52.591 --> 09:54.468
- [whispering]
CHOSEN ONE.

09:54.552 --> 09:55.678
- YOU'RE THE OSIRIAN.

10:00.308 --> 10:02.268
[shimmering tone]

10:02.351 --> 10:03.686
[gasps]

10:03.769 --> 10:04.854
- [exhales heavily]

10:04.937 --> 10:07.898
THINK ABOUT WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

10:08.316 --> 10:10.526
- NO.

10:10.609 --> 10:11.652
NO.

10:11.736 --> 10:13.529
PLEASE DON'T DO THIS.

10:13.612 --> 10:14.280
- FABIAN...

10:14.363 --> 10:16.615
IT'S THE ONLY WAY.

10:16.699 --> 10:18.492
- NO.

10:18.576 --> 10:19.827
[gem clicks]

10:19.910 --> 10:20.703
[shimmering tone]

10:32.548 --> 10:32.673
[gasps]

10:50.483 --> 10:52.234
- LOOK AT THE MASK.

10:52.318 --> 10:55.613
- TEARS OF GOLD.

10:55.696 --> 10:58.616
- [whispering]
CHOSEN ONE.

10:58.699 --> 11:01.243
[cackling]

11:07.708 --> 11:09.377
[shimmering tone]

11:11.170 --> 11:14.006
- THE FIELD OF RUSHES AWAITS...

11:14.090 --> 11:14.882
CHOSEN ONE.

11:26.852 --> 11:28.354
- NINA!
- NINA!

11:28.437 --> 11:28.687
- NINA!

11:32.191 --> 11:32.900
- SOMEBODY DO SOMETHING, PLEASE!

11:32.983 --> 11:34.276
- NINA!
- FABIAN, NO!

11:34.360 --> 11:36.821
[electrical zapping]

11:36.904 --> 11:38.948
- JOY!
- JOY!

11:39.031 --> 11:40.282
- DON'T JUST STAND THERE.
DO SOMETHING!

11:40.366 --> 11:42.076
- [whispering]
OSIRIAN.

11:42.159 --> 11:44.203
- TELL ME WHERE!

11:44.286 --> 11:45.413
- [whispering]
SENKHARA'S CROWN.

11:45.496 --> 11:46.497
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

11:46.580 --> 11:47.248
- RUFUS AND VICTOR
ARE RIGHT BEHIND ME.

11:47.331 --> 11:49.333
WE NEED TO--

11:49.417 --> 11:50.418
- IN THE NAME OF ANUBIS,
I BANISH YOU!

11:50.501 --> 11:53.129
[speaking foreign language]

11:53.212 --> 11:57.007
- OSIRIAN, NO!

11:57.091 --> 11:59.051
[electrical humming]

11:59.135 --> 12:01.011
NO!

12:01.095 --> 12:03.514
[screeching]

12:06.767 --> 12:09.645
- YOU GIVE ME THAT,
YOU LITTLE--

12:09.728 --> 12:11.605
- AH!

12:11.689 --> 12:14.024
- THAT'S THE TRUE MASK.

12:18.988 --> 12:19.905
- NO, NO, NO--

12:19.989 --> 12:20.948
RUFUS, STOP!

12:22.658 --> 12:24.410
- NO--
[screams]

12:24.493 --> 12:25.494
RUFUS, NO!

12:25.578 --> 12:27.329
YOU MUSTN'T WEAR IT!

12:27.413 --> 12:29.540
- LET HIM TAKE IT...

12:29.623 --> 12:30.666
AND GO.

12:30.750 --> 12:31.834
- YOU LISTEN TO THE OLD MAN,
CHILD.

12:31.917 --> 12:35.838
- YES, YOU LISTEN
TO THIS OLD MAN, NINA.

12:35.921 --> 12:36.881
- AH--

12:36.964 --> 12:38.007
AHH!

12:38.090 --> 12:39.258
- NO, RUFUS, STOP!

12:39.341 --> 12:43.220
- PREPARE TO BOW DOWN
BEFORE ME, MORTALS!

12:43.304 --> 12:46.307
[shimmering tone]

12:46.390 --> 12:50.019
[explosion thundering]

12:50.102 --> 12:52.188
- NO!

12:52.271 --> 12:54.732
[wind whooshing]

12:54.815 --> 12:56.859
[glass shattering]

12:56.942 --> 13:00.279
- [demonic voice] YOU KNOW
YOU ARE NOT THE PARAGON.

13:00.362 --> 13:05.242
[screaming]

13:05.326 --> 13:08.621
AHH!

13:08.704 --> 13:10.706
AHHH!

13:13.459 --> 13:16.378
[dramatic music]

13:16.462 --> 13:22.510
♪ ♪

13:24.637 --> 13:26.138
- JOY?

13:26.222 --> 13:28.057
JOY!

13:28.140 --> 13:29.642
- NO.

13:29.725 --> 13:31.018
- I CAN'T FIND A PULSE.

13:31.101 --> 13:32.186
I CAN'T FIND A PULSE!

13:32.269 --> 13:33.938
- LET ME SEE.
STAND BACK!

13:36.315 --> 13:38.067
IT'S THERE,
BUT IT'S VERY FAINT.

13:38.150 --> 13:39.151
- WHAT HAPPENED?

13:39.235 --> 13:40.194
- [sobs]
- WHAT HAPPENED, BOY?

13:40.277 --> 13:42.238
- SHE SAVED ME
FROM THE LIGHTNING BOLT

13:42.321 --> 13:43.405
THAT NINA THREW AT ME.

13:43.489 --> 13:44.740
- HELP ME.
HELP ME.

13:47.493 --> 13:49.620
[shimmering tone]

13:49.703 --> 13:50.955
- [gasps]

13:55.543 --> 13:55.960
- LOOK.

14:00.923 --> 14:03.050
[shimmering]

14:03.133 --> 14:04.885
- TEARS OF GOLD.

14:04.969 --> 14:07.096
THE LAST ONE.

14:07.179 --> 14:10.349
- IT'S THE INGREDIENT
FOR ELIXIR, ISN'T IT?

14:10.432 --> 14:12.476
- YES.

14:12.560 --> 14:14.478
GIVE IT TO ME.

14:17.231 --> 14:19.191
[dramatic music]

14:19.275 --> 14:24.071
♪ ♪

14:24.154 --> 14:26.407
[shimmering tone]

14:26.490 --> 14:35.416
♪ ♪

14:35.499 --> 14:37.793
[shimmering tone]

14:37.876 --> 14:39.795
- [coughing]

14:39.878 --> 14:41.714
[laughter]

14:41.797 --> 14:43.841
- YES, YES!

14:43.924 --> 14:45.426
- [laughs]

14:47.720 --> 14:48.846
- WHAT HAPPENED?

14:48.929 --> 14:50.806
- STUPID HEROICS,
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED.

14:50.889 --> 14:51.473
[laughter]

14:51.557 --> 14:57.021
[thunder rumbling]

14:59.898 --> 15:01.358
- HEY.

15:03.569 --> 15:05.863
- HAS SHE REALLY GONE?

15:05.946 --> 15:08.699
- YEAH.

15:08.782 --> 15:09.867
- [laughs]

15:09.950 --> 15:11.493
MY MARK--IT'S DISAPPEARED.

15:11.577 --> 15:13.495
- MINE TOO.

15:13.579 --> 15:16.206
- [laughs]
- [sighs, laughs]

15:16.290 --> 15:18.667
- SO THAT WAS...

15:18.751 --> 15:20.502
[laughs]
UNBELIEVABLE.

15:20.586 --> 15:22.171
- HOW DID YOU KNOW WHAT TO DO?

15:22.254 --> 15:23.756
- I DON'T KNOW.

15:23.839 --> 15:24.673
IT'S LIKE
SOMEONE WAS TELLING ME,

15:24.757 --> 15:27.635
LIKE, FROM INSIDE MY OWN HEAD.

15:27.718 --> 15:30.054
ROCKED IT, THOUGH, RIGHT?

15:30.137 --> 15:31.305
- [laughs]

15:36.435 --> 15:38.145
[shimmering tone]

15:39.438 --> 15:41.482
- [laughs]

15:42.274 --> 15:44.526
I KNOW WHERE THIS BELONGS.

15:44.610 --> 15:46.445
HEY, WHERE'S JEROME?

15:46.528 --> 15:48.822
- I DON'T KNOW.

15:50.115 --> 15:52.701
SO YOU WERE PRETTY BRAVE
TODAY, ALFIE.

15:52.785 --> 15:53.744
- I KNOW.

15:53.827 --> 15:57.623
UM, I'VE BEEN THINKING...

15:57.706 --> 15:59.708
MAYBE "AMFIE" DOES HAVE
A CERTAIN RING TO IT.

15:59.792 --> 16:02.127
- I THINK YOU MEAN "ALBER."

16:02.211 --> 16:04.254
- ALTHOUGH I MAY HAVE
CERTAIN CONDITIONS...

16:04.338 --> 16:04.963
- YOU HAVE CERTAIN CONDITIONS?

16:07.299 --> 16:07.841
[sighs]

16:07.925 --> 16:09.677
AND I'M CALM.

16:09.760 --> 16:12.721
OKAY, LET'S HEAR THEM.

16:12.805 --> 16:14.556
- WELL, FOR STARTERS,
I'M THINKING MAYBE

16:14.640 --> 16:15.683
MATCHING MONSTER MASKS.

16:15.766 --> 16:16.975
- WHAT?

16:17.059 --> 16:19.269
- WE'D BETTER GET GOING
BEFORE PEOPLE START ASKING

16:19.353 --> 16:21.146
WHERE WE ARE.

16:21.230 --> 16:22.731
YOU COMING?

16:22.815 --> 16:24.066
- YOU GUYS GO AHEAD.

16:24.149 --> 16:25.526
I'LL MEET YOU THERE.

16:25.609 --> 16:27.319
- OKAY.

16:27.403 --> 16:28.445
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

16:37.204 --> 16:39.498
- YOU KNEW
WHAT WOULD HAPPEN TO RUFUS

16:39.581 --> 16:41.083
WHEN HE PUT ON THAT MASK,

16:41.166 --> 16:42.376
DIDN'T YOU?

16:50.050 --> 16:52.344
- ONLY THE PURE OF HEART

16:52.428 --> 16:54.430
MAY ENTER THE AFTERLIFE
AND BECOME A GOD.

16:54.513 --> 16:56.306
- [sighs]

16:56.390 --> 16:57.599
I THINK
WE SHOULD PUT THAT BACK

16:57.683 --> 16:58.934
TO WHERE ROBERT INTENDED IT,

16:59.017 --> 17:00.227
DON'T YOU THINK?

17:09.653 --> 17:11.238
I HAVE SOMETHING FOR YOU.

17:13.656 --> 17:15.492
IT'S FROM YOUR FATHER.

17:19.704 --> 17:21.623
- WHERE ON EARTH...

17:21.707 --> 17:25.127
- HE SAYS, "SORRY."

17:39.767 --> 17:42.728
[dance music]

17:42.811 --> 17:50.819
♪ ♪

17:53.989 --> 17:55.240
- JEROME, WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

17:55.324 --> 17:58.160
YOU DO REALIZE
YOU MISSED YOUR DAD'S HEARING.

17:58.243 --> 17:59.119
- I KNOW.

17:59.203 --> 18:00.496
I TRIED CALLING POPPY.

18:00.579 --> 18:01.330
IT WENT STRAIGHT TO VOICEMAIL.

18:01.413 --> 18:03.540
- I THOUGHT YOU'D CHANGED.

18:03.624 --> 18:05.250
- YOU ARE AMAZING.

18:05.334 --> 18:06.877
HOW DID YOU EVER MANAGE
TO GET THIS BACK

18:06.960 --> 18:09.546
FROM YOU-KNOW-WHO?

18:09.630 --> 18:12.049
YOUR DAD'S GONNA BE
SO PROUD OF YOU.

18:14.259 --> 18:16.011
- THANK YOU.

18:16.095 --> 18:19.139
SERIOUSLY.

18:19.223 --> 18:21.058
BUT I'M NOT SO SURE.

18:21.141 --> 18:22.643
- WH--

18:22.726 --> 18:24.019
OH.

18:24.102 --> 18:25.103
OH...

18:25.187 --> 18:28.023
HEY, LOOK, FOOD!

18:29.983 --> 18:32.486
- IS THAT WHAT I THINK IT IS?

18:34.905 --> 18:35.906
SO THAT'S WHERE YOU'VE BEEN
THIS WHOLE TIME?

18:35.989 --> 18:38.575
WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST TELL ME?

18:38.659 --> 18:40.536
- I DIDN'T WANT YOU TO WORRY.

18:40.619 --> 18:44.039
AND I DIDN'T WANT
TO PUT YOU IN DANGER.

18:49.837 --> 18:51.171
DAD!

18:51.255 --> 18:53.257
- WE DID IT.

19:03.600 --> 19:04.476
- I AM SORRY.

19:04.560 --> 19:05.269
I WANTED TO BE THERE.

19:05.352 --> 19:08.438
- NONE OF THAT MATTERS NOW.

19:10.482 --> 19:11.608
- [laughs]

19:16.113 --> 19:17.614
GIVE ME A MOMENT, OKAY?

19:19.575 --> 19:21.076
MARA.

19:21.159 --> 19:25.664
WILL YOU PLEASE,
PLEASE, PLEASE...

19:25.747 --> 19:29.918
GO OUT WITH ME?

19:30.002 --> 19:34.339
- YES.

19:34.423 --> 19:38.051
- I TOLD YOU.
- I TOLD YOU.

19:38.135 --> 19:39.928
- NO, I TOLD YOU.

19:52.941 --> 19:54.192
- MMM, IT'S GOOD.

19:55.861 --> 19:59.197
- SO, DAD...

19:59.281 --> 20:01.992
YOU EVER HEARD THE WORD...

20:02.075 --> 20:02.618
"OSIRIAN"?

20:02.701 --> 20:05.787
- [coughs]

20:05.871 --> 20:07.039
WHERE DID YOU HEAR THAT?

20:07.122 --> 20:10.292
- I'LL TAKE THAT AS A YES.

20:11.126 --> 20:15.005
IS THAT WHY YOU KEPT ME AWAY?

20:15.088 --> 20:17.466
- LOOK, I'M NOT TELLING YOU
EVERYTHING YOU NEED TO KNOW.

20:17.549 --> 20:18.800
NOT HERE.

20:18.884 --> 20:21.386
AND NOT NOW.

20:30.979 --> 20:32.272
- HEY.

20:32.356 --> 20:33.565
- SO WHERE'S NINA?

20:33.649 --> 20:34.733
- SHE'S WITH HER GRAN.

20:34.816 --> 20:36.068
- OH.

20:36.151 --> 20:38.612
WANT TO DANCE?

20:38.695 --> 20:39.863
- OH, WELL--

20:39.947 --> 20:43.075
- I GET IT,
JUST AS FRIENDS.

20:43.158 --> 20:45.827
- ALL RIGHT, LET'S DANCE.

20:45.911 --> 20:53.961
♪ ♪

20:57.798 --> 20:58.298
WHEN DID YOU GET HERE?

20:58.382 --> 20:59.841
- OH, FABIAN.

20:59.925 --> 21:01.760
- GOOD TO SEE YOU.

21:01.843 --> 21:03.345
- AND YOU.

21:03.428 --> 21:07.933
IF YOU'RE LOOKING FOR NINA,
SHE'S UP THERE.

21:10.560 --> 21:11.311
- GO ON.

21:14.314 --> 21:15.273
- NINA.

21:15.357 --> 21:15.691
- OKAY, WAIT.

21:15.774 --> 21:19.069
WAIT...

21:21.363 --> 21:22.990
WAIT...

21:26.994 --> 21:29.037
I'M CLEAR!

21:29.121 --> 21:30.497
- [laughs]

21:30.580 --> 21:33.709
[dance music playing]

21:33.792 --> 21:35.794
[slow dance music plays]

21:35.877 --> 21:36.461
- [laughs]

21:42.551 --> 21:47.723
- ♪ IT'S THE WAY
YOU MAKE ME FEEL ♪

21:50.142 --> 21:52.561
- I'VE BEEN THINKING.

21:52.644 --> 21:54.479
WE GOT IT ALL WRONG.

21:54.563 --> 21:55.313
- ♪ YOU'RE MY SHINING STAR ♪

21:55.397 --> 21:59.735
- BREAKING UP AND--AND STUFF.

21:59.818 --> 22:01.903
YOU DO KNOW YOU'RE THE ONE,
RIGHT?

22:01.987 --> 22:03.613
- THE CHOSEN ONE.

22:03.697 --> 22:06.491
- WELL, MY CHOSEN ONE.

22:11.413 --> 22:14.624
- YAY!

22:14.708 --> 22:18.837
[all talking excitedly]

22:18.920 --> 22:20.422
FINALLY.

22:20.505 --> 22:21.631
- [laughs]

22:26.011 --> 22:27.471
[shimmering tone]

22:31.433 --> 22:34.394
[dramatic music]

22:34.478 --> 22:38.857
♪ ♪

22:38.940 --> 22:43.028
- TEARS...OF GOLD.

22:48.283 --> 22:51.369
[adventurous music]

22:51.453 --> 22:58.376
♪ ♪
